Which size of egg should I buy?” This is a problem I am glad to see highlighted. British egg sizes are indeed larger than their equals in America. Medium British size = 53g-63g (usually on bigger side) while American medium = 50g. For American recipes requiring “medium” eggs, use British size “small”.
